This paper deals with the probabilistic analysis of hybrid systems, which are systems that combine continuous dynamics (modeled by ODEs) with discrete transitions between modes. This is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses probabilistic methods and Markov chains, which are common tools in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of BLTL (bounded linear time temporal logic) specifications, which is a topic in formal methods (cs.MS) and verification (cs.RO).
